[{'account_id': 9816, 'date': '2021-02-01 03:13:21.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 9816, 'date': '2021-02-01 03:29:12.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Workflow-1'}, {'account_id': 6926, 'date': '2021-02-01 10:23:52.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1

is there a particular issue to solve with this?'}, {'account_id': 11816, 'date': '2021-02-01 15:17:00.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1

I took a quick look to see what it means when there was not previously an "httpchk" option and then one is added.  HAProxy will do an HTTP OPTIONS request to an HTTP server to see if it's up.    

I'm working from no previous background on what I see here, but I would assume that the /healthcheck URL is intended to provide a more comprehensive liveness check for a service than a simple HTTP OPTIONs, such as, if the service can accept HTTP requests but is unable to get to the database.

that seems like a great idea, so from that perspective I can give this the +1.  

other perspectives where I don't really know the answer are:

1. do all the services in question here have support for /healthcheck ?

2. why isn't the change applied to all endpoints that include "mode='http'" such as manila, gnocchi, mistral, swift, ironic, etc. ?      


3. is there any concern that services where /healthcheck is being added have some need to be available from a proxy POV when they are not able to give a full "healthcheck" answer?   like an API that returns a status message as to why the service is down, something like that.    Seems unlikely but I really don't know.'}, {'account_id': 9816, 'date': '2021-04-20 14:35:58.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

> Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1
> 
> I took a quick look to see what it means when there was not previously an "httpchk" option and then one is added.  HAProxy will do an HTTP OPTIONS request to an HTTP server to see if it's up.    
> 
> I'm working from no previous background on what I see here, but I would assume that the /healthcheck URL is intended to provide a more comprehensive liveness check for a service than a simple HTTP OPTIONs, such as, if the service can accept HTTP requests but is unable to get to the database.
> 
> that seems like a great idea, so from that perspective I can give this the +1.  
Yes. That is my general intention of this patch.
Because each service now provides API for healthcheck, there is not reason why we don't use it.
Unfortunately most of the services doesn't implement very deep healthcheck at this moment so all we can validation with this healthcheck api is just only api is responding, but we'd expect that we can leverage future implementation.


> other perspectives where I don't really know the answer are:
> 
> 1. do all the services in question here have support for /healthcheck ?
Yes. 
What I'm trying to implement is switching to /healthcheck about the services
which currently support /healthcheck API.
 
> 2. why isn't the change applied to all endpoints that include "mode='http'" such as manila, gnocchi, mistral, swift, ironic, etc. ?      
I didn't implemented switch about the services which doesn't provide healthcheck API at this moment.
But the situation has been slightly changed so I'll update this patch accordingly.
(though some services like Gnocchi or Mistral still do not support /healthcheck)

> 
> 3. is there any concern that services where /healthcheck is being added have some need to be available from a proxy POV when they are not able to give a full "healthcheck" answer?   like an API that returns a status message as to why the service is down, something like that.    Seems unlikely but I really don't know.
I'm not aware of such use case. commit_message:
haproxy: Use healthcheck middleware to monitor service availability

This change makes that haproxy monitors service availability by sending
HTTP request which is responsed by healthcheck middleware, to ensure
that backend api can respond to requests.

Change-Id: Idbfe6a8e110ec24d9fe64e43d82772bb05fa00ba

haproxy: Use healthcheck API for Ironic and Octavia

According to https://docs.fluentd.org/installation/install-by-deb, in
which said that

> For Ubuntu Focal:
> # td-agent 4
> curl -L https://toolbelt.treasuredata.com/sh/install-ubuntu-focal-td-agent4.sh | sh

in install-ubuntu-focal-td-agent4.sh, it was

>   echo "deb http://packages.treasuredata.com/4/ubuntu/focal/ focal contrib" > /etc/apt/sources.list.d/treasure-data.list

As for bionic

> For Ubuntu Bionic:
> # td-agent 4
> curl -L https://toolbelt.treasuredata.com/sh/install-ubuntu-bionic-td-agent4.sh | sh
> # td-agent 3
> curl -L https://toolbelt.treasuredata.com/sh/install-ubuntu-bionic-td-agent3.sh | sh

In conclustion, td-agent did not provide version 3 endpoint for ubuntu
focal, kolla sources.list example should adapt that update.

Signed-off-by: FredericDT <frederic.dt.twh@gmail.com>
Change-Id: Iee311b60485dc0bb53960700979ada93e4b755b4

commit_message:
Allow to set pacemaker cluster properties

There is no ways to set pacemaker stonith-timeout values to something
different than the default values.   This change would allow a user
to set any pacemaker cluster properties using PacemakerProperties.

  PacemakerProperties:
    'stonith-timeout':
      property: 'stonith-timeout'
      value: '120s'

Change-Id: Ied77623953fd97dce7de1d529e98d5483a42e31b

Closes-Bug: #1867925

Remove workaround for openstackclient < 4.0.0

mixing usage of master puppet-keystone and such old openstackclient is
not supported.

commit_message:
Add horizontal scrollbar to role dropdown

Manage members dialog has a dropdown which lists all the role names.
If a role name is long enough, it pushes all the roles to the left
and hides them partially. This patch adds horizontal scrollbar for
such cases.

Closes-Bug: #1926511

Change-Id: I1bbf3b23717f9924974920d6569e018b94e3dbe8
